      • newTransportRequest

        public static StreamingHttpRequest newTransportRequest(HttpRequestMethod method,
                                                       java.lang.String requestTarget,
                                                       HttpProtocolVersion version,
                                                       HttpHeaders headers,
                                                       BufferAllocator allocator,
                                                       Publisher<java.lang.Object> payload,
                                                       HttpHeadersFactory headersFactory)
        Creates a new StreamingHttpRequest which is read from the transport. If the request contains trailers then the passed payload Publisher should also emit HttpHeaders before completion.
        Parameters:
        method - the HttpRequestMethod of the request.
        requestTarget - the request-target of the request.
        version - the HttpProtocolVersion of the request.
        headers - the HttpHeaders of the request.
        allocator - the allocator used for serialization purposes if necessary.
        payload - a Publisher for payload that optionally emits HttpHeaders if the request contains trailers.
        headersFactory - HttpHeadersFactory to use.
        Returns:
        a new StreamingHttpRequest.
